

	 
      Once again, the internet helps speed up processes that would normally take months if done in person.  This  urlLink article  states how the internet is a well used  tool when adoptive parents are looking for potential adoptive children. However, this article also reminds us not to always trust what we find on the internet.  Some adoption sites have been known to be started by false agencies that are just looking for ways to earn money.  Checking references is vital if someone is using the internet for something as important as adopting a child.   
     

    
